article.headline: Ball St. 88, Valparaiso 78
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Six Ball State players scored in double figures, led by Jarrod Jones who had 19 points, and the Cardinals defeated Valparaiso 88-78 Friday in the season opener for both teams. Malik Perry finished with 17, Jauwan Scaife had 14, Brawley Chisholm 12 and Terrence Watson and Randy Davis each added 11, marking the first time Ball State has had six players score in double figures since Feb. 7, 1998 against Bowling Green. Brandon Wood led the Crusaders with 25 points, and Cory Johnson had 21. Ball State led 42-38 at halftime and outshot Valparaiso 57.8-42.9 percent from the field for the game. The Cardinals are now 40-9 all-time in home openers.
